
Ubuntu 18.04

Before install:

wget -qO - https://download.sublimetext.com/sublimehq-pub.gpg | sudo apt-key add -
sudo systemctl disable systemd-networkd-wait-online.service
wget -qO - https://downloads.iridiumbrowser.de/ubuntu/iridium-release-sign-01.pub | sudo apt-key add -
echo "deb [arch=amd64] https://downloads.iridiumbrowser.de/deb/ stable main" | sudo tee --append /etc/apt/sources.list.d/iridium-browser.list 
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:saiarcot895/chromium-beta

Packages:

sublime-text xterm feh redshift volumeicon-alsa tp-smapi-dkms xfce4-terminal zsh fonts-roboto-fontface fonts-roboto lightdm lightdm-gtk-greeter lightdm-gtk-greeter-settings i3 ubuntu-drivers-common mesa-utils mesa-utils-extra xorg xserver-xorg xserver-xorg-video-intel intel-microcode i3blocks remmina lm-sensors ranger mupdf firefox vlc chromium-browser pulseaudio pulseaudio-utils pavucontrol pulseaudio-module-bluetooth blueman network-manager-gnome pasystray arandr cmake pkg-config



Polybar
sudo apt-get install cmake cmake-data libcairo2-dev libxcb1-dev libxcb-ewmh-dev libxcb-icccm4-dev libxcb-image0-dev libxcb-randr0-dev libxcb-util0-dev libxcb-xkb-dev pkg-config python-xcbgen xcb-proto libxcb-xrm-dev i3-wm libasound2-dev libmpdclient-dev libiw-dev libcurl4-openssl-dev libpulse-dev libxcb-composite0-dev xcb libxcb-ewmh2

git clone https://github.com/jaagr/polybar.git

cd polybar && ./build.sh

sudo apt install unifont
git clone https://github.com/stark/siji && cd siji

edit etc/X11/xinit/xinitrc
add this:
xset fp+ /home/basil/.fonts/



Manual install

sudo snap install spotify
sudo snap install discord 

browser extensions
	vimium 
	darken(dark mode nightreader) 
	font changer 
	arc dark theme


After Install

sudo modprobe tp_smapi
sudo update-alternatives --config x-terminal-emulator 
systemctl disable systemd-networkd-wait-online.service





